@alexche8 
interfaces work just fine with graphene-django, just include your interface in your interfaces tuple under the meta class of your DjangoObjectType

http://docs.graphene-python.org/en/latest/types/interfaces/

I'll give you an example that I use in my project
```python
class FileNodeInterface(graphene.Interface):
    id = graphene.GlobalID()
    url = graphene.String()
    is_display = graphene.Boolean()
    is_pdf = graphene.Boolean()
     

class ImageNode(DjangoObjectType):
    def resolve_url(self, args, request, info):
        return self.image.url

    def resolve_is_pdf(*_):
        return False


    class Meta:
        interfaces = (Node, FileNodeInterface)
        model = MasterlistingImages


class FlyerNode(DjangoObjectType):

    def resolve_url(instance, args, request, info):
        return instance.file.url
    
    def resolve_is_pdf(*_):
        name = instance.file.name
        return name[-3:] == 'pdf'



    class Meta:
        interfaces = (Node, FileNodeInterface)
        model = MasterlistingFlyers
```

